<br>
My name is Radha. I am a young Wood Elf Druid of 16th season and would like to join this wonderful guild.<br>
<br>
I have been looking at a few different guilds to become a member of as I enjoy playing with a good group of folks instead of alone. To me thats why you play a multiplayer game.<br>
<br>
I found out about AW from wandering the roads of Faydwer and asking for direction to Lyri and Adlehardt. Not only did they tell me what I needed to know, but they took the time and escorted me to the zone I was going to; killing a few Sand Giants on the way. I would love to become associated with a good group that has noble members like this.<br>
<br>
I am located in the east coast of USA in the city of New York. I am normaly on from 9 PM EST to about 1 AM EST on weekdays, and on weekends I am on whenever I get a chance to. <br>
<br>
I love to play in good groups and with strategies. Everyone knowing what they are suppose to do makes for a real enjoyable gaming experience to me. I also love the questing aspects of a game. I always help group members whenever I can. I never leave a group if someone has died and doesnt have their corpse back. <br>
<br>
I hope the introduction wasn't too long. I look forward to chatting with more AW members and becoming a part of this fine tradition.<br>
<br>
Radha<br>
